  "name": "Fibromyalgia - Pain Medication Query (Duloxetine + Gabapentin + Amitriptyline)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find fibromyalgia patients via duloxetine (SNRI), gabapentin (gabapentinoid), or amitriptyline (TCA). All three are highly cross-indicated: duloxetine for depression/anxiety/diabetic neuropathy; gabapentin for epilepsy/neuropathic pain; amitriptyline for depression/migraine prophylaxis/insomnia.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed duloxetine, gabapentin, or amitriptyline for chronic pain management.",
